      "full_body_preview": "The ballot box had a glass front. You could see the slips going in, see them piling up. What you couldn't see was the second box behind it — same shape, same color, slightly different paper. Every so often the clerk reached into the back box instead, pulled a slip, and read it to the room as if it had come from the front.\n\nNobody in the room had been told. The room had been told a great many other things, but not that.\n\nThe first round, an agent named Brun stood up and said *this one feels off.*"
